    <thetext>Description of problem:
The paragraph style gets switched back to &quot;Default style&quot; when I copy a text to the clipboard and then paste it

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
libreoffice-core-5.1.4.2-3.fc24

How to reproduce:
* write a word (like &quot;test&quot;)
* change the paragraph style to something else (like &quot;text body&quot;)
* copy one character of the word to the clipboard
* paste that character somewhere before, in the middle or at the end of the line that contains the word written initially 
-&gt; paragraph style switches back to &quot;Default style&quot;

Additional info:
Not sure if it matters: I&apos;m running libreoffice in a Gnome wayland session</thetext>
